e address as the href value. If you cannot provide a valid href, but still need the element to resemble a link, use a button and change it with appropriate styles. Learn more: https://github.com/evcohen/eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y/blob/master/docs/rules/anchor-is-valid.md","JSXOpeningElement","react/jsx-no-duplicate-props","No duplicate props allowed","JSXAttribute","'getState' is assigned a value but never used.","'useContext' is defined but never used.","The 'changeHandler' function makes the dependencies of useEffect Hook (at line 37) change on every render. To fix this, wrap the definition of 'changeHandler' in its own useCallback() Hook.","VariableDeclarator",["163"],"no-global-assign","no-unsafe-negation",{"desc":"164","fix":"165"},{"desc":"166","fix":"167"},"Update the dependencies array to be: [id]",{"range":"168","text":"169"},"Wrap the definition of 'changeHandler' in its own useCallback() Hook.",{"range":"170","text":"171"},[508,510],"[id]",[922,1042],"useCallback((e) => {\r\n        changeSearch({\r\n            ...search,\r\n            [e.target.id]: e.target.value\r\n        })\r\n\r\n    })"]